  "worklog": "## 2026-03-30 04:10 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] VWAP Filter Killing Profitable Trades at Peak Hours\n\n**Task:** Analyze why the PM bot executed only 1 trade on Saturday Mar 29 despite active hours having signals. Determine if conviction/VWAP filters are too aggressive.\n\n**Finding:** VWAP_DISAGREES filter is blocking high-WR trades at our best hours:\n- **11h UTC:** 12 YES signals blocked by VWAP. Hour's actual WR = 88% (7W/1L). Estimated missed profit: +$41.\n- **12h UTC:** 8 YES signals blocked by VWAP. Hour's actual WR = 82% (14W/3L). Estimated missed profit: +$21.\n- **19h UTC:** 1 blocked. WR = 75%. Minimal impact.\n- **20h UTC:** 6 blocked. WR = 58%. VWAP filter is protective here (-$8 if allowed).\n- LOW_CONVICTION also blocked 15 YES signals at 12h, 8 at 11h, 8 at 19h.\n- Saturday Mar 29: 70 signals were NO_TRADE_SKIPPED (positive bias = NO direction, V3.2 correctly blocks).\n\nThe VWAP stats (54% vs 45% WR) were computed across ALL hours. But 11h and 12h have structural edge (London session, clean signals) where VWAP disagree doesn't matter \u2014 prices move our way regardless.\n\n**Mar 28 (Friday) results:** 6 trades total. 5 at 09h (before V3 active hours deployed): 2W/3L. 1 at 19h: WIN. Validates cutting 09h.\n\n**My thinking:** The VWAP filter was correct as a universal gate when we traded all hours. But now we only trade 4 golden hours. At 11h (88% WR) and 12h (82% WR), the edge is so strong that VWAP disagreement is noise \u2014 we're leaving ~$62/week on the table. At 20h (58% WR), VWAP filtering is protective. Hour-specific filter thresholds are the play.\n\n**Decision:** Design V4 hour-adaptive filters:\n- 11h + 12h: Relax VWAP gate (allow trades if 2/3 other indicators agree, regardless of VWAP)\n- 19h + 20h: Keep VWAP mandatory (lower WR hours need all confirmation)\n- Need to backtest this against full Mar 23-28 data before deploying.\n\n**Also fixed:** PM bot screen was dead (crashed ~01:03 UTC). Restarted as LIVE in screen \"pm-bot\".\n\n**Next P2 heartbeat:** Backtest V4 hour-adaptive VWAP relaxation. Quantify exact WR impact from confidence_outcomes.jsonl by simulating: \"what if VWAP-blocked trades at 11h/12h were executed?\"\n\n## 2026-03-30 03:38 UTC \u2014 Pillar 1: STRONG_TREND Alert + Position Check\n\n**REGIME ESCALATED: 5/8 \u2192 7/8 (STRONG_TREND) in 30 min**\n\nBTC rallying hard: $66,289 \u2192 $67,178 (+1.3%) since midnight. Direction consistency jumped to 88% UP. Range crossed 2.0% threshold. All 4 regime components now contributing points.\n\n**Score breakdown (7/8):**\n- ATR 1.38% (+1) \u2014 elevated vol\n- DIR 88% UP (+2) \u2014 strong directional consensus\n- RNG 2.07% (+2) \u2014 wide range broke threshold\n- TRD +1.41% (+2) \u2014 clear uptrend\n\n**HL positions:** Account $364.61. All 3 still green (+$2.00 total uPnL).\n- BTC LONG(!) size=0.00162 entry=$66,836 uPnL=+$0.51\n- Note: entry prices differ from MEMORY.md \u2014 may have been adjusted by funding or partial fills. Need to verify.\n\n**Revised RANGE ETA:** 08:00-10:00 UTC at earliest. BTC must fully exhaust this rally AND consolidate for 4+ hours",
